  "prompt": "What universities does Pall recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Pall Corporation, a global leader in filtration, separation, and purification technologies (now part of Danaher Corporation), typically recruits new graduates from a variety of universities and in fields aligned with their business needs. While the specific universities and majors Pall recruits from can vary over time, here\u2019s a general idea based on their industry and focus:\n\n### **Universities**\nPall often recruits from **top-tier universities** and **technical institutes** globally, including:\n\n1. **U.S. Universities**:\n   - Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)\n   - Stanford University\n   - University of California, Berkeley\n   - Georgia Institute of Technology\n   - Cornell University\n   - Purdue University\n   - University of Michigan\n   - University of Wisconsin-Madison\n\n2. **International Universities**:\n   - University of Cambridge (UK)\n   - Imperial College London (UK)\n   - ETH Zurich (Switzerland)\n   - National University of Singapore (NUS)\n   - Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs, India)\n\nPall also partners with universities that have strong engineering and life sciences programs, as these align closely with their business operations.\n\n---\n\n### **Majors**\nPall looks for graduates with technical and scientific expertise. The most sought-after majors typically include:\n\n1. **Engineering**:\n   - Chemical Engineering\n   - Mechanical Engineering\n   - Biomedical Engineering\n   - Materials Science and Engineering\n\n2. **Life Sciences**:\n   - Biochemistry\n   - Biotechnology\n   - Microbiology\n   - Molecular Biology\n\n3. **Other Relevant Fields**:\n   - Chemistry\n   - Environmental Science\n   - Industrial Engineering\n   - Supply Chain Management (for operations roles)\n\n---\n\n### **Recruitment Process**\nPall often recruits through:\n- **Career fairs** at universities with strong engineering and life sciences programs.\n- **Internship programs** that convert to full-time roles.\n- **On-campus interviews** and partnerships with university career centers.\n\nIf you\u2019re a student or recent graduate interested in Pall, it\u2019s best to check their official career page or LinkedIn for current opportunities and recruitment details.",
